On Fri, May 21, 2004 at 10:01:43AM -0400, cdavid wrote:
> Does the tank need to come out to do this or is the process
> accomplished with the tank in the bus?

Best to remove it.  To get the chemicals to coat the inside of the
tank well you need to be able to turn it upside down, side to side
etc.  

You'd probably want to get a new O-ring seal for the gas guage
sender unit as you ordinarilly remove that as well.

